1. The statement is about a sub-analysis of adherence rates for patients who attended at least 2 follow-up visits.
2. The adherence rate for patients in G1 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 91.3%.
3. The number of patients in G1 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 23, out of which 21 adhered.
4. The adherence rate for patients in G2 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 74.3%.
5. The number of patients in G2 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 35, out of which 26 adhered.
6. The adherence rate for patients in G3 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 66.7%.
7. The number of patients in G3 who attended at least 2 follow-up visits was 27, out of which 18 adhered.
8. The P-value for the comparison of adherence rates among the three groups is 0.11.

messages.content:
Statement: Sub-analysis of adherence rates for patients who attended ≥2 follow-up visits were 91.3% (n=21/23) for G1, 74.3% (n=26/35) for G2, and 66.7% (n=18/27) for G3, (P=0.11).
